\

\b How do I run Quick Setup?
\b0 \
After Victory is installed and you are logged into your site, the first step is to run Quick Setup.  In your WP Dashboard, Go to the Victory options panel, make sure that quick setup is checked (it is checked by defautl) and click the "run quick setup button."\
Quick Setup is optional but it is highly recommended as it pre-populates pages, menus and default settings so your website is 95% finished in seconds.  Quick setup saves time and avoids configuration so all you have to do is edit.\
\

\b How do I set up my blog?
\b0 \
First, create a page where your blog will live (i.e. blog, my thoughts, ramblings). In your WP dashboard, go to Settings => Reading => drop down the Posts Page and select the name of your blog page.  All posts that you create will be added to your blog.\
\
\

\b How do I change the colors of different site elements?
\b0 \
If you are a developer, you can enter custom CSS into the CSS box.  For testing your CSS changes, we recommend that you use Google Developer Tools or Firefox.\
In our next version of Victory we will include more color customization for non-developers.\
\
