\b Sidebar & Widgets
\b0 \
\

\b How do I set up the Action Buttons in the sidebar?
\b0 \
Go to your WordPress dashboard, go to Widgets and drop down the Primary Aside widget area.  Dropdown the Victory Action Buttons widget.  You can modify the button's title and select a page for the user be directed to upon click.  To direct the user to an external site, select "Other (provide external url)" and paste in your external URL in the field that appears.\
\

\b How do I set up the Facebook Widget?
\b0 \
Go to your WordPress dashboard, go to Widgets and dropdown the Primary Aside widget area.  Dropdown the Facebook Widget and paste in your Facebook Page ID or Facebook Page URL. After you set your Facebook Widget options, click save.  Note, for the Facebook Widget to work, you must have a Facebook Page ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.facebook.com/FacebookPages"}}{\fldrslt http://www.facebook.com/FacebookPages}}).  A Facebook Profile will not work.  To learn more about WordPress Widgets, go to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.facebook.com/FacebookPages"}}{\fldrslt http://www.facebook.com/FacebookPages}}\
\

\b Why is my Facebook Widget not working?
\b0 \
In order to use the Facebook widget, you must have a facebook page for your campaign or candidate.  A Facebook profile will not work.\
\

\b How do I set up the Twitter Widget?
\b0 \
Go to your WordPress dashboard, go to Widgets and dropdown the Primary Aside widget area.  Dropdown the Twitter Widget and paste in your Twitter username (i.e. your Twitter Handle).  After setting your Twitter options, click save.  To learn more about WordPress Widgets, go to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.facebook.com/FacebookPages"}}{\fldrslt http://www.facebook.com/FacebookPages}}\
\

\b How do I modify the Social Media Icons in the sidebar?
\b0 \
Go to your WordPress dashboard, go to Widgets and dropdown the Primary Aside widget area.  Dropdown the Social Media Icons widget and paste in your URL for each social media service that you use.  The default icons that show up have a URL of "#" which is an HTML placeholder.  If you do not want an icon to appear, simply delete any text within the icon input box.  If the social media icon box is blank, no icon will appear.\
