\b Slider
\b0 \
\

\b What is the Nivo Slider for?
\b0 \
The Nivo Slider is for images only.  You can may also add captions to each slide in the Nivo slider. \
Your images should be cropped appropriately (the dimensions can be found in the slider section).  Images that are too big will cause breaks in your page, creating a strange appearance.  Images that are too small will look awkward because blank space will be leftover.\
For images only, use the Nivo Slider.\
\

\b What is the Anything Slider for?
\b0 \
Well, anything really!  The Anything Slider is for a combination of images and video slides.  Anything allows you to include Youtube or Vimeo videos in your slider in addition to image slides.\
For images only use Nivo, for images and video use the Anything; pretty simple.\
\

\b How do I resize my slider images?
\b0 \
If you have Photoshop check out this tutorial: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yzFZVKF21lU&feature=related"}}{\fldrslt http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yzFZVKF21lU&feature=related}}\
If you don't have Photoshop, download and install GIMP (it's free!) {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.gimp.org/"}}{\fldrslt http://www.gimp.org/}}\
And watch this GIMP tutorial on cropping and resizing photos:  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2rGGpOTSpbc"}}{\fldrslt http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2rGGpOTSpbc}}\
\

\b Why is my slider caption below/outside my slider?
\b0 \
If your slider caption is in an odd position, it's 99% likely that you didn't crop your slider image to the correct dimension before uploading it.  Check the dimensions on the slider type you have selected and crop the photos to match the size listed in the the slider secdtion.\
\

\b How many images should I have in my slider?
\b0 \
For the Nivo Slider, use four to five images at most.  Any more images and your site performance and load time will suffer.  If you are using the Anything Slider, we recommend having one video slide and two to three image slides; any more than that and your site performance and load time will suffer.\
\

